text: Thryptomene hubbardii is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae that is endemic to Western Australia. The shrub is found in the Mid West region of Western Australia between the Chapman Valley and Geraldton where it grows in sandy soils. ==References== hubbardii Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Vulnerable flora of Australia Category:Plants described in 2014 Category:Taxa named by Barbara Lynette Rye Category:Taxa named by Malcolm Eric Trudgen
